<item>
            <title>[QPID-5342] Java client ignores missing heartbeats</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-5342</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Java JMS client for AMQP 0.10 doesn&apos;t seem to detect missing heartbeats. In the logs it is visible that the client is responding to the heartbeats received from the broker. But when I suspend the broker, the client doesn&apos;t mind that no heartbeats are received. I would expect that the client should detect missing heartbeats and timeout the connection after 2 heartbeat intervals.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;(tested with C++ broker)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
